-- Sample Book Data for Library Management System
-- 15 diverse books across different categories

INSERT INTO Books (Title, Author, Description, Category) VALUES
('To Kill a Mockingbird', 'Harper Lee', 'Set in the American South during the 1930s, this Pulitzer Prize-winning novel explores themes of racial injustice and moral growth through the eyes of young Scout Finch. Her father, Atticus, a principled lawyer, defends a black man falsely accused of rape, teaching his children about courage and compassion.', 'Novel'),

('1984', 'George Orwell', 'A dystopian masterpiece set in a totalitarian society ruled by Big Brother. Winston Smith works at the Ministry of Truth, rewriting history to fit the Party''s narrative. When he begins a forbidden love affair and starts questioning the regime, he faces the full horror of a surveillance state that controls even thoughts.', 'Science Fiction'),

('The Da Vinci Code', 'Dan Brown', 'Harvard symbologist Robert Langdon is summoned to the Louvre Museum where a curator has been murdered, leaving cryptic clues. Joined by cryptologist Sophie Neveu, Langdon uncovers a trail of secrets hidden in the works of Leonardo da Vinci, leading to revelations that could shake the foundations of Christianity.', 'Mystery'),

('Steve Jobs', 'Walter Isaacson', 'Based on over forty interviews with Jobs conducted over two years, as well as interviews with family members, colleagues, and competitors, this authorized biography provides an unprecedented look at the creative entrepreneur whose passion for perfection revolutionized six industries: personal computers, animated movies, music, phones, tablet computing, and digital publishing.', 'Biography'),

('Sapiens: A Brief History of Humankind', 'Yuval Noah Harari', 'From the evolution of Homo sapiens in the Stone Age to the political and technological revolutions of the twenty-first century, this groundbreaking narrative explores how biology and history have defined us and enhanced our understanding of what it means to be human. Harari examines our capacity for imagination and cooperation.', 'History'),

('Atomic Habits', 'James Clear', 'A practical guide to breaking bad habits and building good ones through tiny changes that deliver remarkable results. Clear reveals proven strategies including the Four Laws of Behavior Change, habit stacking, and the two-minute rule. Learn why tiny changes make a big difference and how to design your environment for success.', 'Self-Help'),

('Clean Code', 'Robert C. Martin', 'Even bad code can function. But if code isn''t clean, it can bring a development organization to its knees. This essential handbook presents a comprehensive guide to writing clean, readable, and maintainable code. Packed with practical examples and real-world case studies, it teaches software craftsmanship principles.', 'Technology'),

('The Great Gatsby', 'F. Scott Fitzgerald', 'Set in the Jazz Age on Long Island, this novel tells the story of Jay Gatsby, a mysterious millionaire who throws lavish parties in pursuit of his lost love, Daisy Buchanan. Narrator Nick Carraway witnesses the tragic consequences of obsession, wealth, and the American Dream in this timeless classic.', 'Novel'),

('One Hundred Years of Solitude', 'Gabriel García Márquez', 'The multi-generational story of the Buendía family in the fictional town of Macondo, blending magical realism with political and social commentary. From the founding of the town to its apocalyptic end, Márquez weaves a narrative about love, fate, and the cyclical nature of history in Latin America.', 'Translation'),

('Dune', 'Frank Herbert', 'On the desert planet Arrakis, young Paul Atreides must navigate political intrigue, ecological challenges, and his own prophetic visions after his family is betrayed. This epic tale of politics, religion, and ecology has become one of the most influential science fiction novels ever written, spawning an entire universe.', 'Science Fiction'),

('And Then There Were None', 'Agatha Christie', 'Ten strangers are lured to an isolated island mansion. When a recorded message accuses each of murder, they realize they have been brought to the island to pay for their crimes. As they are murdered one by one, following the pattern of a nursery rhyme, the survivors must determine the killer''s identity before it''s too late.', 'Mystery'),

('The Diary of a Young Girl', 'Anne Frank', 'The remarkable diary of a teenage Jewish girl hiding from the Nazis in Amsterdam during World War II. Anne''s honest, sometimes humorous observations about adolescence, relationships, and hope in the face of persecution have made her story one of the most widely read accounts of the Holocaust.', 'Biography'),

('The Art of War', 'Sun Tzu', 'This ancient Chinese military treatise, dating from the 5th century BC, remains the most influential strategy text in East Asian warfare. Its thirteen chapters offer timeless wisdom on tactics, strategy, and leadership that has been applied to business, sports, diplomacy, and everyday life for centuries.', 'History'),

('The 7 Habits of Highly Effective People', 'Stephen R. Covey', 'A holistic approach to personal and professional effectiveness through seven habits: be proactive, begin with the end in mind, put first things first, think win-win, seek first to understand, synergize, and sharpen the saw. Covey presents a principle-centered approach for solving personal and professional problems.', 'Self-Help'),

('The Pragmatic Programmer', 'Andrew Hunt and David Thomas', 'Your Journey to Mastery - This classic guide examines the core process of developing software, from requirements gathering to maintenance. It covers topics ranging from personal responsibility and career development to architectural techniques for keeping code flexible and easy to adapt and reuse.', 'Technology');
